# Figma-to-Code Workflow

## Step-by-step

1. **Fetch design data** — Use Figma MCP `get_figma_data` tool with the file URL or node ID the user provides.
2. **Map colors** — Match Figma fills/strokes to existing `globals.css` tokens. Do not introduce new color values.
3. **Map spacing** — Convert Figma px to Tailwind scale: 4px = `1`, 8px = `2`, 12px = `3`, 16px = `4`, 24px = `6`, 32px = `8`, 48px = `12`.
4. **Map typography** — Use Tailwind text utilities (`text-xs` 12px, `text-sm` 14px, `text-base` 16px, `text-lg` 18px, `text-xl` 20px). Font is Inter via `--font-sans`.
5. **Build component** — Write TSX using Tailwind classes, following `react-components.mdc` conventions.
6. **Verify** — Compare key measurements (widths, padding, font sizes, border radii) against the Figma spec.

## Color mapping reference

| Figma token | Tailwind class |
|-------------|---------------|
| Dark background | `bg-background` |
| Card / panel fill | `bg-surface` |
| Input / hover fill | `bg-surface-light` |
| Borders | `border-border` |
| Primary text | `text-foreground` |
| Secondary text | `text-muted` |
| Accent / brand | `text-primary`, `bg-primary` |
| Purple accent | `text-accent` |
| Error / danger | `text-danger` |
| Star / rating | `text-star` |

## Constraints

- Never add new CSS color variables — if a Figma color doesn't map, pick the closest existing token.
- All spacing via Tailwind utilities, no hardcoded px in `style` attributes.
- If Figma MCP is not connected, work from screenshots or user descriptions instead and note the limitation.
